  "texts": [
    "Precisely speaking, we solve the following problem: Given two molecular graphs M 1 and M 2, and a distance threshold T, compute their minimum weighted distance w(M 1, M 2) if this is below T and otherwise an (ideally large) lower bound for d(M 1, M 2).",
    "We solve this problem using an algorithm engineering approach.",
    "It consists of first computing lower bounds on the distance.",
    "Should the maximum of these bounds already be larger than T, we report this maximum.",
    "Only if both bounds fail, we use an exact algorithm based on an integer linear program (ILP) to compute minfdðM 1, M 2 Þ, Tg."
  ],
